---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<PageLayout title="Scalar Effects" slug="sketches/scalar-effects">

<section class="demo-section" id="pixel-orbit">
<div class="demo-header">
<h2>Pixel Orbit</h2>
<a href={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/01-pixel-orbit/index.html`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">open full size ↗</a>
</div>
<div class="demo-embed">
<iframe src={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/01-pixel-orbit/index.html?embedded`} title="Pixel Orbit" scrolling="no" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>
  Each pixel computes its own camera position on a ring around the target, displaced laterally by the
  FFT value at the angular frequency matching that pixel's screen angle. At silence all cameras
  collapse to the same position. On a loud chord with distributed spectral energy, opposite sides of
  the screen see opposite faces — the shape appears to shatter into a prism of simultaneous perspectives.
</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="demo-section" id="spectral-warp">
<div class="demo-header">
<h2>Spectral Warp</h2>
<a href={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/02-spectral-warp/index.html`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">open full size ↗</a>
</div>
<div class="demo-embed">
<iframe src={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/02-spectral-warp/index.html?embedded`} title="Spectral Warp" scrolling="no" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>
  Before evaluating the SDF, the domain point <code>p</code> is displaced by a vector field that is
  the sum of eight sinusoidal components — one per FFT band octave. Each component has a spatial
  frequency proportional to its audio frequency. The warp is divergence-free in some components and
  compressive in others, so parts of the surface fold inward while others balloon outward
  simultaneously, with spatial periods matched to the audio spectrum.
</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="demo-section" id="4d-section">
<div class="demo-header">
<h2>4D Section</h2>
<a href={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/03-4d-section/index.html`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">open full size ↗</a>
</div>
<div class="demo-embed">
<iframe src={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/03-4d-section/index.html?embedded`} title="4D Section" scrolling="no" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>
  A gyroid is defined in four spatial dimensions. The 3D scene evaluates this field at a rotating 4D
  orientation — the <em>xw</em> rotation plane driven by accumulated bass phase, the <em>yw</em> plane
  by treble. The 3D cross-section of a 4D surface changes topology as it rotates: handles appear,
  surfaces pinch off, disconnected sheets merge. The audio controls which topological state is
  revealed at each moment.
</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="demo-section" id="spectral-lensing">
<div class="demo-header">
<h2>Spectral Lensing</h2>
<a href={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/04-spectral-lensing/index.html`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">open full size ↗</a>
</div>
<div class="demo-embed">
<iframe src={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/04-spectral-lensing/index.html?embedded`} title="Spectral Lensing" scrolling="no" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>
  Before the ray marcher runs, each pixel's ray direction is perturbed by a multi-scale oscillating
  field. Eight frequency bands each contribute a transverse push whose spatial frequency on screen
  matches the audio frequency band. Low frequencies create broad, slow-moving lens distortions; high
  frequencies create fine ripples on the shape's surface. The combined effect resembles gravitational
  lensing through a medium whose refractive index varies with the music's spectral content.
</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="demo-section" id="temporal-smear">
<div class="demo-header">
<h2>Temporal Smear</h2>
<a href={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/05-temporal-smear/index.html`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">open full size ↗</a>
</div>
<div class="demo-embed">
<iframe src={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/05-temporal-smear/index.html?embedded`} title="Temporal Smear" scrolling="no" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>
  Each pixel composites four time-offset renders of the same scene. The time offset scales with
  overall amplitude, but is not uniform across the screen — it varies by position, driven by bass on
  the horizontal axis and treble on the vertical. Different screen regions live at different moments
  in time, bending the shape through its own animated history.
</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="demo-section" id="ifs-fold">
<div class="demo-header">
<h2>IFS Fold</h2>
<a href={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/06-ifs-fold/index.html`} target="_blank" rel="noopener">open full size ↗</a>
</div>
<div class="demo-embed">
<iframe src={`${base}/sketches/scalar-effects/06-ifs-fold/index.html?embedded`} title="IFS Fold" scrolling="no" allow="autoplay"></iframe>
</div>
<div class="prose">
<p>
  Iterated octahedron and box folds are applied to the domain before SDF evaluation. Each fold
  reflects space across a plane, creating recursive self-similarity at decreasing scales. Amplitude
  drives the number of fold iterations — at silence the shape is clean; at peak loudness six folds
  accumulate and the surface becomes a fractal tangle. Midrange controls the fold scale, setting the
  size ratio between recursive copies.
</p>
</div>
</section>

</PageLayout>
